class AppDescriptions {
  static const String descriptions = """
The key particularity of the project is the creation of the Broiyalty mobile application to identify three types of diseases in chickens – Coccidiosis, Newcastle Disease, and Salmonella – by examining feces using the YOLOv8 algorithm. The disease detection app will be designed to provide users with personalized interfaces that enable them to take pictures of diseases or upload existing ones. The Disease Detection Module will offer prognosis and recommendations regarding the findings, while in the Learning Module, the users will be able to find information on various chicken diseases and treatments. Functionalities of the app maintainability, performance efficiency, reliability, functional suitability, usability, security, compatibility, and portability will be evaluated based on ISO 25010 standards.
""";
